### Closira API Tests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension

@base = http://localhost:8000

### 1. Health Check
GET {{base}}/health

### 2. Create pricing enquiry (matches Pricing Question SOP)
POST {{base}}/enquiry
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "whatsapp",
  "customer_name": "Sarah Mitchell",
  "message": "Hi I want to know your pricing for the premium plan"
}

### 3. Create booking enquiry (matches Booking Enquiry SOP)
POST {{base}}/enquiry
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "email",
  "customer_name": "Raj Verma",
  "message": "I want to book an appointment for next Monday"
}

### 4. Create complaint (matches Complaint SOP)
POST {{base}}/enquiry
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "call",
  "customer_name": "Priya Sharma",
  "message": "I am very upset and want a refund immediately"
}

### 5. Create no-match enquiry (auto-escalates)
POST {{base}}/enquiry
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "whatsapp",
  "customer_name": "Test User",
  "message": "zxqzxq random gibberish"
}

### 6. Get enquiry history (replace ID with real one)
GET {{base}}/enquiry/enq_8b3678eb/history

### 7. Schedule follow-up
POST {{base}}/enquiry/enq_8b3678eb/followup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "delay_minutes": 30,
  "message_template": "Hi Sarah, just following up on your enquiry!"
}

### 8. Escalate enquiry
POST {{base}}/enquiry/enq_f56a4412/escalate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Customer called back and is very upset"
}

### 9. Invalid channel - should return 422
POST {{base}}/enquiry
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "telegram",
  "customer_name": "Test",
  "message": "hello"
}

### 10. Non-existent enquiry - should return 404
GET {{base}}/enquiry/enq_doesnotexist/history